# Daily Harness Usage (BUSCA-CNPJ-2026)

Project root: `/data/dev/projects/webstorm/BUSCA-CNPJ-2026`

## One-time setup

```bash
cd /data/dev/projects/webstorm/BUSCA-CNPJ-2026
pip install -r agent-harness/requirements.txt
```

## Start of every non-trivial task

```bash
cd /data/dev/projects/webstorm/BUSCA-CNPJ-2026
./agent-harness/rules-path.sh
./agent-harness/resolve-rules.sh <keywords from task>
```

**Keyword examples:**

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| API / handlers | `./agent-harness/resolve-rules.sh api performance security` |
| Import / DB | `./agent-harness/resolve-rules.sh query migration performance` |
| Security review | `./agent-harness/resolve-rules.sh owasp security injection` |
| Bug fix | `./agent-harness/resolve-rules.sh bugfix regression error` |

Read only the listed files under `agent-rules/` — not the entire tree.

## Cursor: temporary task rule (optional)

Generate at task start:

```bash
./agent-harness/generate-task-rules.sh api export
# or: api performance security, domain layer, etc.
```

Creates `.cursor/rules/_task-active.mdc` (`alwaysApply: false`).

**Cleanup when task is done (MANDATORY):**

```bash
./agent-harness/generate-task-rules.sh --clean
# or: rm .cursor/rules/_task-active.mdc
```

## Agent session checklist

1. Open project in Cursor — rules in `.cursor/rules/` load automatically.
2. Read `AGENTS.md` if context is empty.
3. Run `resolve-rules.sh` for the task keywords.
4. Optionally run `generate-task-rules.sh`.
5. State which rule files you loaded.
6. On task end: `--clean` temporary task rule.

## Paths

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `agent-rules/` | Harness rule library |
| `agent-harness/` | Scripts (`resolve-rules`, `generate-task-rules`) |
| `.agent-harness/` | Git submodule (update: `git submodule update --remote .agent-harness`) |
| `docs/GLOSSARY.md` | Domain terms |
